// Semantic direction:
// ui_stdlib is the Norscode standard UI library: widgets, layout, theme, animation, and input.
// view is a composable UI component defined by a view_fn that maps view_state and view_props to a widget tree.
// view_body is the widget tree returned by view_fn for the current state.
// dirty_check compares view_state to its previous value and skips re-rendering if unchanged.
// memoize_view caches the view_body for a given props hash and reuses it without calling view_fn.
// use_state declares a state_value local to a view and returns a set_state function.
// use_effect runs a side effect after the view renders; effect_deps lists the values it depends on.
// effect_cleanup runs when deps change or the view unmounts, to cancel subscriptions or timers.
// use_ref holds a mutable value that does not trigger re-renders when changed.
// context_provide makes a context_value available to all descendant views without passing it as props.
// context_consume reads the nearest ancestor's context_value.
// signal is a reactive primitive: any view that reads signal_value is re-rendered when it changes.
// computed_signal derives a new value from one or more signals and memoizes the result.
// batch_update groups multiple signal_set calls into one re-render.
// virtual_list renders only the visible portion of a large list, recycling off-screen views.
// virtual_overscan renders a few extra rows beyond the visible virtual_window to avoid blank flicker.
// form provides unified field validation; field_touched prevents errors from showing before interaction.
// form_validate_fn is called on submit; it returns form_errors per field name.
// a11y_role assigns a semantic ARIA role for screen readers (button, heading, list, alert).
// a11y_live_region marks a region whose content updates are announced by screen readers.
// screen_reader_text adds visually hidden text for accessibility without cluttering the visual layout.
// cmd_ui_preview launches a live preview of a view component in a window.
// cmd_ui_storybook starts an interactive gallery of all registered components with their variants.

// Primitive flow:
// view cycle: use_state(initial) -> view_fn(state, props) -> widget_tree
//   user action -> set_state(new) -> dirty_check -> re-render view_body
// signal: signal_set(new) -> notify dependents -> rerender affected views
//   batch_update: multiple sets -> one rerender
// virtual_list: scroll event -> new virtual_window -> render visible items + overscan
//   recycle: off-screen views returned to pool -> new items take recycled views
// form: field onChange -> set field_value + field_touched
//   on submit -> form_validate_fn -> form_errors -> show per-field error or submit
// nc ui preview MyView.no -> hot-reload window showing component variants
// nc ui test -> headless render + assert widget tree matches snapshot

// This defines the Norscode UI stdlib: reactive views, state hooks, signals,
// virtual lists, forms, accessibility, and developer tooling commands.
